title: Binance is sued by another US regulator, sparking plunge in cryptocurrency values and shares
description: US regulators have filed a lawsuit against cryptocurrency exchange Binance, alleging a string of violations including the misuse of investor funds.

title: Russia 'diverting attention' by claiming Ukraine counteroffensive - Kyiv
description: Russian reports that the Ukrainian counteroffensive has begun are being used to distract from Russian losses in Bakhmut, the Ukrainian deputy defence minister has said.

title: What does online evidence reveal about Ukraine's 'large-scale offensive'?
description: The Russian Ministry of Defence has claimed that Ukraine launched a "large-scale offensive" in the south of the Donetsk region.

title: 'Senior member' of Kinahan crime group arrested while eating at Spanish restaurant
description: A suspected senior member of the Kinahan cartel has been arrested while eating at a restaurant in Spain.

title: Businessman walks over 2,600 miles from London to Istanbul to promote carbon capture
description: A businessman-turned-activist has walked more than 2,600 miles through 14 countries as part of his climate campaign to promote carbon capture.

title: Oil boss running COP28 under pressure to present plan
description: Pressure is mounting on the UAE oil boss running international climate negotiations this year to convince his critics he has a suitably ambitious plan, as diplomats meet in Germany this week for preparatory talks.

title: Investigation into deadly India train crash begins as rail services resume
description: Rail services have resumed over a stretch of the railway network in eastern India where a train crash killed 275 people - as an investigation into the disaster began.

title: Children may have died due to 'incredibly rare' genetic mutation - as imprisoned mum pardoned
description: British scientists found an "incredibly rare" genetic mutation could have been responsible for the deaths of two children after their mother, who was originally jailed for killing them, has now been pardoned.

title: Woman jailed for 20 years over deaths of her four children is pardoned
description: A woman jailed for 20 years over the deaths of her four children has been pardoned after a judicial review.

title: Nearly 80 schoolgirls poisoned in Afghanistan
description: Nearly 80 girls have been poisoned and hospitalised in two separate attacks at their primary schools in Afghanistan, an official has said.

title: People who got used to face masks during COVID attend smiling lessons
description: People in Japan who became so used to wearing face masks during the pandemic are signing up for lessons to teach them how to smile again.
